00:07:55.560 --> 00:07:58.080
Let's talk about workspace optimization.

00:07:58.080 --> 00:08:01.490
This is a topic that's intrigued
me for a very long time

00:08:01.490 --> 00:08:05.670
because my undergraduate
advisor, my graduate advisor

00:08:05.670 --> 00:08:09.050
and my postdoc advisor
had many things in common,

00:08:09.050 --> 00:08:11.700
including being great
scientists, being kind people

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:14.300
and terrific mentors, but they
had another thing in common,

00:08:14.300 --> 00:08:17.130
which always perplexed me,
which is that their offices

00:08:17.130 --> 00:08:19.220
were a complete disaster.

00:08:19.220 --> 00:08:22.560
They had mountains of
books, mountains of papers,

00:08:22.560 --> 00:08:24.410
mountains of all sorts of stuff.

00:08:24.410 --> 00:08:27.420
And yet all of them were
extremely productive

00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:29.280
and could remain extremely focused

00:08:29.280 --> 00:08:31.760
in that incredibly cluttered environment.

00:08:31.760 --> 00:08:33.420
Now I'm somebody who doesn't like clutter,

00:08:33.420 --> 00:08:36.090
I find it very hard to focus
in cluttered environments.

00:08:36.090 --> 00:08:39.040
And indeed there's tremendous
variation among people

00:08:39.040 --> 00:08:40.760
as to whether or not
they can remain focused

00:08:40.760 --> 00:08:42.180
or whether or not they struggle to focus

00:08:42.180 --> 00:08:44.540
in physically cluttered environments.

00:08:44.540 --> 00:08:46.220
There's no right or wrong to this,

00:08:46.220 --> 00:08:47.480
but the question we should ask ourselves

00:08:47.480 --> 00:08:50.170
is why were they all
able to be so focused?

00:08:50.170 --> 00:08:52.650
And it turns out that
the reason they were able

00:08:52.650 --> 00:08:56.560
to be so focused is that
they all captured one single

00:08:56.560 --> 00:09:00.120
and yet fundamental variable
of workspace optimization.

00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:02.260
And we'll talk about
what that variable is.

00:09:02.260 --> 00:09:05.080
In fact, where you're to talk
about what all the variables

00:09:05.080 --> 00:09:08.320
of optimizing a workspace
are things like vision,

00:09:08.320 --> 00:09:10.810
things like light, things
like noise in the room,

00:09:10.810 --> 00:09:12.380
whether or not you listen to music or not,

00:09:12.380 --> 00:09:15.870
whether or not you use noise
canceling headphones or not.

00:09:15.870 --> 00:09:17.890
We're going to talk about all of that

00:09:17.890 --> 00:09:20.010
and we're going to do that in a way

00:09:20.010 --> 00:09:21.670
that you can optimize your workspace,

00:09:21.670 --> 00:09:23.670
regardless of whether
or not you are at home,

00:09:23.670 --> 00:09:25.810
whether or not you're
on the road, et cetera.

00:09:25.810 --> 00:09:28.210
Because the last thing
I would ever want to do

00:09:28.210 --> 00:09:30.610
is to create a situation where you find

00:09:30.610 --> 00:09:33.410
the optimal workspace,
and then you are a slave

00:09:33.410 --> 00:09:34.640
to that optimal workspace.

00:09:34.640 --> 00:09:36.110
That's just not the way the world works.

00:09:36.110 --> 00:09:38.950
What you want to do or
my goal for you rather,

00:09:38.950 --> 00:09:40.870
is that you will have a
short checklist of things

00:09:40.870 --> 00:09:43.860
