tell me pat your head kind of thing.

01:33:54.930 --> 01:33:56.750
But it still feels like a little bit

01:33:56.750 --> 01:34:01.090
of a sort of a cognitive
motor collision for me

01:34:01.090 --> 01:34:03.160
for whatever reason,
but that's just my bias.

01:34:03.160 --> 01:34:05.140
I do know how to ride
a bicycle, but anyway,

01:34:05.140 --> 01:34:06.530
you pick your preference.

01:34:06.530 --> 01:34:07.810
Some other things that you could do

01:34:07.810 --> 01:34:10.670
in order to improve your
workplace performance

01:34:10.670 --> 01:34:13.100
would be to consider the cathedral effect.

01:34:13.100 --> 01:34:16.210
If you're going to do analytic
work for any part of the day,

01:34:16.210 --> 01:34:18.200
phase one or phase two,
as I described them,

01:34:18.200 --> 01:34:21.450
but really in any time of day,
that detailed analytic work

01:34:21.450 --> 01:34:23.310
for which there is a correct answer,

01:34:23.310 --> 01:34:25.380
learning scales of music,
learning mathematics,

01:34:25.380 --> 01:34:27.220
trying to figure out the
solution to a problem

01:34:27.220 --> 01:34:28.720
where there is indeed a solution.

01:34:28.720 --> 01:34:31.110
It could be an interpersonal
problem as well,

01:34:31.110 --> 01:34:32.620
then try and get into an environment

01:34:32.620 --> 01:34:34.140
with a relatively low ceiling.

01:34:34.140 --> 01:34:36.120
If you don't have access to
a low ceiling environment,

01:34:36.120 --> 01:34:39.070
you might consider using a
brimmed hat or even a hoodie,

01:34:39.070 --> 01:34:41.950
or even just facing down,
or even putting your hand

01:34:41.950 --> 01:34:46.142
above your eyes, as you will,
at the level of your eyebrows.

01:34:46.142 --> 01:34:48.300
In other words, lower the
ceiling, that's the basis

01:34:48.300 --> 01:34:52.022
of the cathedral effects
on analytic performance.

01:34:52.022 --> 01:34:55.860
In contrast, if you're interested
in doing brainstorming,

01:34:55.860 --> 01:34:59.140
creative work, you're writing new things,

01:34:59.140 --> 01:35:01.350
you're creating new things
of any kind, artwork,

01:35:01.350 --> 01:35:02.860
consider getting into a high ceiling

01:35:02.860 --> 01:35:05.760
or no ceiling environment,
or if you're wearing

01:35:05.760 --> 01:35:07.230
a brimmed hat or you're wearing a hoodie,

01:35:07.230 --> 01:35:08.960
maybe peel that back.

01:35:08.960 --> 01:35:12.040
Again, the data within the
peer reviewed literature

01:35:12.040 --> 01:35:14.920
are there to support
these sorts of practices.

01:35:14.920 --> 01:35:16.730
And if you'd like to start
layering these protocols,

01:35:16.730 --> 01:35:18.480
by all means, please do that.

01:35:18.480 --> 01:35:20.637
There's no reason why you couldn't do one

01:35:20.637 --> 01:35:22.980
or just two of these protocols.

01:35:22.980 --> 01:35:24.370
There's no reason why, for instance,

01:35:24.370 --> 01:35:26.980
you couldn't use binaural
beats and try and get

01:35:26.980 --> 01:35:29.640
into a low ceiling environment
to do detailed work

01:35:29.640 --> 01:35:30.760
a couple times a week,

01:35:30.760 --> 01:35:33.040
but you could also employ all of these.

01:35:33.040 --> 01:35:35.360
Now, of course, there are an
