01:35:35.360 --> 01:35:37.890
that you can do to
improve work performance

01:35:37.890 --> 01:35:39.680
and productivity, and
I've talked about those

01:35:39.680 --> 01:35:41.120
in previous episodes, in particular,

01:35:41.120 --> 01:35:44.620
in the episode on focus and
the episode on motivation,

01:35:44.620 --> 01:35:46.560
there are supplements you can take

01:35:46.560 --> 01:35:48.270
that can increase dopamine, for instance.

01:35:48.270 --> 01:35:51.650
There are tools that you can
use to increase your focus,

01:35:51.650 --> 01:35:54.010
for instance, focusing
your visual attention

01:35:54.010 --> 01:35:56.750
on one location for 30 to 60 seconds

01:35:56.750 --> 01:35:58.770
prior to entering a focused work about,

01:35:58.770 --> 01:36:00.600
this has been shown again and again.

01:36:00.600 --> 01:36:03.240
The work from Emily Bell, that's at NYU

01:36:03.240 --> 01:36:05.710
in the episode on focus, I
cited a number of studies

01:36:05.710 --> 01:36:06.930
where this has actually been tested

01:36:06.930 --> 01:36:08.870
and deployed in various schools.

01:36:08.870 --> 01:36:11.540
Having kids do a focus
task where they look

01:36:11.540 --> 01:36:13.770
at a particular visual
target for 30 to 60 seconds,

01:36:13.770 --> 01:36:15.950
then doing some mathematics and seeing

01:36:15.950 --> 01:36:18.380
pretty impressive improvement
in focus and attention,

01:36:18.380 --> 01:36:20.470
even in people that
have attention deficit,

01:36:20.470 --> 01:36:22.830
hyperactivity disorder and so on.

01:36:22.830 --> 01:36:26.300
So there's no reason why you
can't and shouldn't combine

