01:37:27.400 --> 01:37:29.070
I have a brief anecdote about this.

01:37:29.070 --> 01:37:31.230
I used to attend a lot
of scientific meetings

01:37:31.230 --> 01:37:33.600
when a lot of scientific
meetings were in person,

01:37:33.600 --> 01:37:35.395
and there were always a few individuals

01:37:35.395 --> 01:37:37.030
that seem to stay engaged

01:37:37.030 --> 01:37:38.897
throughout these very long meetings.

01:37:38.897 --> 01:37:40.750
And we're talking seven, eight hour day,

01:37:40.750 --> 01:37:44.410
sometimes evening sessions,
and sometimes these meetings

01:37:44.410 --> 01:37:47.530
would go on for, four or
five or even six days.

01:37:47.530 --> 01:37:49.970
These are long meetings
and the quality of talks

01:37:49.970 --> 01:37:52.610
vary tremendously, and I
always notice the individuals

01:37:52.610 --> 01:37:54.970
that manage to stay engaged and awake

01:37:54.970 --> 01:37:57.410
for the entire meeting.

01:37:57.410 --> 01:38:00.560
And I noticed that people
that could maintain

01:38:00.560 --> 01:38:03.770
high levels of alertness
in this one conference room

01:38:03.770 --> 01:38:06.590
had a habit of moving to a different seat

01:38:06.590 --> 01:38:09.200
after each session,
sometimes even between talks.

01:38:09.200 --> 01:38:11.290
And I actually discussed this
with one of my colleagues

01:38:11.290 --> 01:38:13.690
who was doing this, I
said, is this conscious,

01:38:13.690 --> 01:38:14.730
are you always moving from place to place?

01:38:14.730 --> 01:38:16.450
And he said, yeah, if I
just stay in one place

01:38:16.450 --> 01:38:18.470
and I just look from this
one particular visual angle

01:38:18.470 --> 01:38:20.650
of the screen, I find
after one or two talks,

01:38:20.650 --> 01:38:23.170
regardless of how
interesting the talks are,

01:38:23.170 --> 01:38:26.050
that I start take on of draft,
my mind isn't as engaged

01:38:26.050 --> 01:38:27.470
and indeed, sometimes can fall asleep.

01:38:27.470 --> 01:38:29.110
And so I started this practice of moving

01:38:29.110 --> 01:38:31.210
from space to space, or I should say,

01:38:31.210 --> 01:38:33.620
seat to seat within an auditorium
and it works quite well.

01:38:33.620 --> 01:38:35.930
And I think it works
quite well because again,

01:38:35.930 --> 01:38:38.630
of the relationship
between our visual system

01:38:38.630 --> 01:38:40.773
driving the majority of our cognition,

01:38:40.773 --> 01:38:43.017
our visual system drives our thinking

01:38:43.017 --> 01:38:45.960
and that novel visual environments

01:38:45.960 --> 01:38:47.070
are going to lend themselves

01:38:47.070 --> 01:38:49.340
to heightened levels of alertness.

01:38:49.340 --> 01:38:51.570
Now, you don't want things
to be so novel and scary

01:38:51.570 --> 01:38:53.810
or threatening or
anxiety-provoking or loud

01:38:53.810 --> 01:38:55.790
that they draw your attention
away from your work.

01:38:55.790 --> 01:38:58.580
But I think this is part of
the reason why turning on music

01:38:58.580 --> 01:39:02.390
or moving to an office or a
cafe or an outdoor environment

01:39:02.390 --> 01:39:04.550
from an indoor environment or vice versa,

01:39:04.550 --> 01:39:06.910
maybe even within a single
day, can bring about

01:39:06.910 --> 01:39:09.010
more heightened levels of productivity.

